'''Aiden Brady''' (also known as '''Aiden Shaw''')<ref name="CoolBoy">{{cite web|url=http://www.bangandstrike.com/bangtalk/coolboy-of-the-week-aiden-shaw/|title=CoolBoy Of The Week- Aiden Shaw |publisher=Bang Talk Magazine|date=24 Feb 2016|first=Sarah|last=Potter|accessdate=7 Oct 2017}}</ref><ref name="Aiden">{{cite book|title= Aiden|last= Beard|first=Mark |author2= Brady, Aiden|year= 1992|publisher= Feard Press |location= London, England|asin= B0006P9EYM}}</ref> is an author, musician, model and former pornographic film actor.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.gay.net/fashion-grooming/2012/03/26/former-adult-star-aiden-shaw-stylish-daddy | publisher=Gay.net | title=Aiden Shaw article | accessdate=5 December 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924020912/http://www.gay.net/fashion-grooming/2012/03/26/former-adult-star-aiden-shaw-stylish-daddy | archive-date=24 September 2015 | dead-url=yes | df=dmy-all }}</ref>

==Pornography==
Brady changed his name to "Shaw" when began working in gay pornography in the early 1990s<ref name="CoolBoy"/> and appeared in over 50 films.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.washingtonblade.com/2009/12/11/aiden-shaw-on-surviving-porn-prostitution/| publisher=Washington Blade| title=Aiden Shaw on surviving porn, prostitution |date=Dec 11, 2009| first=Tyrone| last=Ford| accessdate=6 June 2015}}</ref> He retired from the porn industry in 1999. But in 2004, he starred in another gay porn film with [[Hot House Entertainment|Hot House]].<ref>{{cite web| title=Perfect Fit (2004) |publisher=IMDB |url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0455681/| accessdate=7 Oct 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| title=Perfect Fit | publisher=Hot House| url=http://www.hothouse.com/en/dvd/Perfect-Fit/7911| accessdate=7 Oct 2017}}</ref>

==Writing==
In 1991, Shaw collaborated with the New York artist [[Mark Beard (artist)|Mark Beard]] to produce a limited edition publication named ''Aiden''. The book included several portraits of Shaw, with text written by both Beard and Shaw as a form of dialogue.<ref name="Aiden"/>

Shaw published his first novel, ''Brutal'', in 1996. Also in 1996, The Bad Press published a collection of his poems, ''If Language at the Same Time Shapes and Distorts our Ideas and Emotions, How do we Communicate Love?''<ref name=Shaw1996 >{{citation |last=Shaw |first=Aiden |year=1996 |title=If language at the same time shapes and distorts our ideas and emotions, how do we communicate love?|series=Bemis/Flaherty Collection of Gay Poetry |publisher=The Bad Press |oclc=298124621}}</ref> He wrote two more novels; ''Boundaries'' (1997) and ''Wasted'' (2001), and an autobiography, ''My Undoing'' (2006) in which he openly discusses his life in the sex industry as a porn star and sex worker, his drug use, and his HIV status (Shaw was diagnosed HIV positive in 1997).<ref>{{cite web|author=Josh Sparber |url=http://www.poz.com/articles/1666_9609.shtml |title=The Porn Identity (interview with Aiden Shaw) |publisher=Poz.com |date= September 2006 |accessdate=12 July 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Sam Page |url=http://www.hivplusmag.com/Story.asp?id=2033&categoryid=1 |title=Coming To Terms (interview with Aiden Shaw) |publisher=HIVPLUSMAG.com |date=January 2010 |accessdate=12 July 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100504170034/http://www.hivplusmag.com/Story.asp?ID=2033&categoryid=1 |archivedate=4 May 2010 }}</ref>

==Modeling==
Shaw was signed to Success Models in Paris and Sight Management Studio in Barcelona.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sight-management.com/gallery/model/2831-Aiden+Shaw| publisher=Sight-Management.com| title=Profile - Aiden Brady|accessdate=7 Oct 2017}}</ref> Shaw was shot by Giampaolo Sgura for Hercules International magazine.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://accidentalbear.com/stunning-aiden-shaw-by-giampaolo-sgura-for-hercules-universal-magazine/| publisher=AccidentalBear.com | title=Aiden Shaw by Giampaolo Sgura For Herculese Universal Magazine | accessdate=5 December 2015}}</ref> In 2013 he was the face of the Polish fashion company Bytom.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.thefashionisto.com/aiden-shaw-anatol-modzelewski-bytom-fallwinter-2013-campaign/ | publisher=The Fashionisto | title=Aiden Shaw & Anatol Modzelewski for Bytom| accessdate=7 December 2015}}</ref> In 2014, Shaw walked for [[Berluti]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://models.com/work/berluti-berluti-ss-14-show |publisher=Models.com |title=Berluti Show SS14 – List of Models |accessdate=7 December 2014}}</ref> Shaw was featured by New Zealand menswear brand, Working Style for their Autumn Winter 2014 campaign.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.workingstyle.co.nz/blog/Aiden-Shaw-and-our-AW14-Campaign?i=12|publisher=Working Style|title=Aiden Shaw and our AW14 Campaign|accessdate=27 March 2015}}</ref> In 2016, Shaw reverted to his birth name as he continued to model for international brands like [[Massimo Dutti]].<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.thefashionisto.com/massimo-dutti-2016-mens-contemporary-tailoring/| publisher=TheFashionisto.com| title=Noah Mills, Hao Yun Xiang & Aiden Brady Don Massimo Dutti’s Contemporary Tailoring| date=21 Sep 2016| accessdate=7 Oct 2017}}</ref>

